ld dashboard MVP\n\nSuccess:\n✅ 95% install success\n✅ < 5 min setup\n✅ 100 GitHub stars\n```\n\n### Month 2: Growth (April)\n```\nWeek 5-6: Cloud platform, billing\nWeek 7-8: Community, content\n\nSuccess:\n✅ 500 GitHub stars\n✅ 100 Discord members\n✅ $1K MRR\n```\n\n### Month 3: Enterprise (May)\n```\nWeek 9-10: Security, compliance\nWeek 11-12: Pilot program\n\nSuccess:\n✅ 1,000 users\n✅ 3 pilots\n✅ $5K MRR\n```\n\n---\n\n## Laws of Simplicity\n\n### 1. REDUCE\n```\nSubtract the obvious\nWhat can we remove?\n```\n\n### 2. ORGANIZE\n```\nStructure clearly\n3 phases, 3 tiers\n```\n\n### 3. TIME\n```\nSave time, feel simple\n2-min setup, instant queries\n```\n\n### 4. LEARN\n```\nKnowledge = simplicity\n5-min tutorial, clear docs\n```\n\n### 5. DIFFERENCES\n```\nContrast creates clarity\nOpen vs commercial\n```\n\n### 6. CONTEXT\n```\nPeriphery matters\nCommunity → trust → sales\n```\n\n### 7. EMOTION\n```\nFeel more, think less\n\"Wow, that was easy!\"\n```\n\n### 8. TRUST\n```\nTransparency\nOpen code, clear pricing\n```\n\n### 9. FAILURE\n```\nAccept some complexity\nGit, compliance can't be simple\n```\n\n### 10. THE ONE\n```\nSubtract + Add\nRemove obvious, add meaningful\n```\n\n---\n\n## What We Do\n\n```\n✅ AI code attribution\n✅ Decision traces\n✅ Context graph\n✅ Team memory\n✅ Enterprise governance\n```\n\n## What We DON'T Do\n\n```\n❌ Code quality (SonarQube)\n❌ Productivity metrics (LinearB)\n❌ AI model monitoring (Arize)\n❌ General memory (Notion)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Competitive Moat\n\n```\n1. Execution path (git commits)\n2. Network effects (more users = better patterns)\n3. Open trust (transparent core)\n4. First mover (no one else doing this)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Success Metrics\n\n### Month 1\n```\n100 GitHub stars\n10 cloud users\n95% install success\n```\n\n### Month 2\n```\n500 GitHub stars\n100 Discord members\n50 cloud teams\n$1K MRR\n```\n\n### Month 3\n```\n1,000 active users\n3 enterprise pilots\n$5K MRR\nFirst case study\n```\n\n---\n\n## Weekly Rhythm\n\n```\nMonday: Plan (3 priorities)\nTue-Thu: Build (one thing at a time)\nFriday: Ship & Review\n```\n\n---\n\n## Decision Framework\n\n```\nBefore adding anything, ask:\n\n1. Does it help 1,000 users goal?\n2. Can we explain it in one sentence?\n3. Can we ship it in one week?\n4. Will we maintain it forever?\n5. Is it the simplest solution?\n\n3+ Yes → Do it\n<3 Yes → Skip it\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Principles\n\n### For Product\n```\n1. One job: Answer \"why\" about AI code\n2. Two modes: Local (free) or Cloud (paid)\n3. Three commands: install, sync, ask\n4. Zero config: Works out of the box\n5. Clear upgrade: Hit limit → pay\n```\n\n### For Code\n```\n1. Small modules (<300 lines)\n2. Clear interfaces\n3. Minimal dependencies\n4. Simple storage (SQLite → Redis → PostgreSQL)\n5. Test everything (80% coverage)\n```\n\n### For Business\n```\n1. Transparent pricing\n2. Honest communication\n3. Community first\n4. Sustainable growth\n5. No lock-in\n```\n\n---\n\n## The Mantra\n\n> **Subtract the obvious, add the meaningful.**\n\n**Remove:**\n- Complex features\n- Confusing options\n- Unnecessary code\n\n**Add:**\n- Clear errors\n- Helpful suggestions\n- Delightful moments\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps (This Week)\n\n```\n□ Add MIT LICENSE file\n□ Update README with open source strategy\n□ Fix installation issues\n□ Write getting started guide\n□ Set up Discord community\n```\n\n---\n\n## Contact & Resources\n\n```\nGitHub: github.com/AI-Provenance/devmemory\nDiscord: (coming soon)\nTwitter: @devmemory (coming soon)\nEmail: founders@devmemory.ai\n\nDocs: This repo + /docs folder\nStrategy: PRODUCT_STRATEGY.md\nPlan: IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_90_DAYS.md\nPrinciples: SIMPLICITY_PRINCIPLES.md\nOpen Source: OPEN_SOURCE_STRATEGY.md\n```\n\n---\n\n**Remember:**\n\n> **Simple products win.**  \n> **Open source builds trust.**  \n> **Sustainable businesses last.**\n\n---\n\n*Version 1.0 | March 1, 2026*\n",
