rep\n\n#### Week 9-10: Optimization\n\n**Focus:** Performance & reliability\n\n**Tasks:**\n```\nWeek 9:\n- [ ] API performance optimization\n- [ ] Caching layer\n- [ ] Database optimization\n- [ ] Monitoring setup\n\nWeek 10:\n- [ ] Error tracking\n- [ ] Automated alerts\n- [ ] Backup strategy\n- [ ] Documentation for API\n```\n\n---\n\n#### Week 11-12: Enterprise Features\n\n**Focus:** Prepare for pilots\n\n**Security:**\n```\n- [ ] HTTPS everywhere\n- [ ] API key encryption\n- [ ] Audit logging\n- [ ] Security documentation\n```\n\n**Enterprise Basics:**\n```\n- [ ] Higher rate limits\n- [ ] Team management\n- [ ] Usage analytics\n- [ ] Support system\n```\n\n**Pilot Program:**\n```\n- [ ] Create pilot landing page\n- [ ] Identify 10 target companies\n- [ ] Outreach campaign\n- [ ] Onboard 3 pilots\n```\n\n---\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n### Package Changes\n\n#### Remove\n```bash\n# Delete these files:\ndevmemory/attribution/redis_storage.py\ndevmemory/core/ams_client.py\ndocker-compose.yml\n\n# Update these files:\nrequirements.txt  # Remove redis, ams deps\npyproject.toml    # Update dependencies\n```\n\n#### Add\n```python\n# New file: devmemory/attribution/cloud_storage.py\nimport requests\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nclass CloudStorage:\n    \"\"\"HTTP client for DevMemory Cloud API\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, api_key: str, base_url: str = \"https://api.devmemory.ai\"):\n        self.api_key = api_key\n        self.base_url = base_url\n        self.session = requests.Session()\n        self.session.headers.update({\n            \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\",\n            \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n        })\n    \n    def search(self, query: str, limit: int = 10) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"Search via API\"\"\"\n        response = self.session.post(\n            f\"{self.base_url}/search\",\n            json={\"query\": query, \"limit\": limit}\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()[\"results\"]\n    \n    def get_stats(self) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Get usage stats\"\"\"\n        response = self.session.get(f\"{self.base_url}/stats\")\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n    \n    # ... other methods\n```\n\n#### Update\n```python\n# devmemory/attribution/storage.py\nclass AttributionStorage:\n    def __init__(self, storage_type: str = \"sqlite\", api_key: Optional[str] = None):\n        self.storage_type = storage_type\n        \n        if storage_type == \"sqlite\":\n            self._storage = SQLiteStorage()\n        elif storage_type == \"cloud\":\n            if not api_key:\n                raise ValueError(\"Cloud mode requires API key. Get one at devmemory.ai\")\n            self._storage = CloudStorage(api_key)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unknown storage type: {storage_type}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## CLI Changes\n\n### New Commands\n```bash\n# Cloud mode setup\ndevmemory install --mode cloud --api-key YOUR_API_KEY\n\n# Cloud commands (call API)\ndevmemory search \"why this code?\"\ndevmemory stats\ndevmemory dashboard  # Opens web UI\n\n# Local commands (work offline)\ndevmemory attribution lookup <file>\ndevmemory sync\ndevmemory status\n```\n\n### Configuration\n```yaml\n# .devmemory/config.yaml\nmode: local  # or cloud\napi_key: \"\"  # required for cloud\napi_url: \"https://api.devmemory.ai\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Specification (MVP)\n\n### Authentication\n```http\nPOST /auth/login\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"...\"\n}\n\nResponse:\n{\n  \"api_key\": \"dev_abc123\",\n  \"plan\": \"pro\"\n}\n```\n\n### Search\n```http\nPOST /search\nAuthorization: Bearer dev_abc123\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"query\": \"why this code?\",\n  \"limit\": 10\n}\n\nResponse:\n{\n  \"results\": [...],\n  \"quota_remaining\": 9500\n}\n```\n\n### Stats\n```http\nGET /stats\nAuthorization: Bearer dev_abc123\n\nResponse:\n{\n  \"ai_percentage\": 45,\n  \"human_percentage\": 55,\n  \"total_commits\": 150\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Success Metrics\n\n### Month 1 (March)\n```\n✅ Package < 5MB\n✅ Install time < 2 min\n✅ Local mode works offline\n✅ No Redis dependencies\n✅ 100 GitHub stars\n```\n\n### Month 2 (April)\n```\n✅ API deployed and working\n✅ Dashboard live\n✅ First 10 paying users\n✅ $1K MRR\n✅ 500 GitHub stars\n```\n\n### Month 3 (May)\n```\n✅ 1,000 total users\n✅ 50 cloud users\n✅ 3 enterprise pilots\n✅ $5K MRR\n✅ Stable API (99% uptime)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Risk Mitigation\n\n### Technical Risks\n\n**Risk: API downtime**\n- Local mode always works\n- Clear error messages\n- Retry logic\n- Status page\n\n**Risk: Breaking changes for existing users**\n- Migration guide\n- Deprecation warnings\n- Backward compatibility (Month 1)\n- Clear communication\n\n### Business Risks\n\n**Risk: Users don't want API-based**\n- Local mode is full-featured for basic needs\n- Emphasize convenience of cloud\n- On-premise option for enterprise (later)\n\n**Risk: API costs too high**\n- Efficient implementation\n- Caching\n- Usage optimization\n\n---\n\n## Communication Plan\n\n### To Users\n```markdown\n## DevMemory 0.2.0: Simplified Architecture\n\nWe've streamlined DevMemory into a single package:\n\n**Local Mode** (Free Forever)\n- pip install devmemory\n- SQLite storage\n- Works offline\n- Core attribution\n\n**Cloud Mode** (devmemory.ai)\n- API key required\n- Advanced features\n- Team collaboration\n- Subscribe at devmemory.ai\n\n**Why the change?**\n- Simpler installation\n- No infrastructure to manage\n- Clear value proposition\n- Better performance\n\n**Migration:**\nExisting users: Your local data is preserved. Cloud mode now uses our API instead of self-hosted Redis.\n```\n\n### Timeline\n```\nWeek 1-2: Development\nWeek 3-4: Testing & docs\nWeek 5: Announce upcoming change\nWeek 6: Release v0.2.0\nWeek 7: Cloud API beta\nWeek 8-12: Iterate based on feedback\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Architecture:** Single package, API-based cloud\n\n**Month 1:** Remove Redis/AMS, add API client, clean docs\n**Month 2:** Launch API, dashboard, billing\n**Month 3:** Scale, enterprise prep, pilots\n\n**Success:** 1,000 users, $5K MRR, clean architecture\n\n---\n\n*Version: 2.0 (Single Package Architecture)*  \n*Date: March 1, 2026*  \n*Next Review: Weekly during Month 1*\n",
